There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit
There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit
There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit

There company E employees working town T work for. The employees live N towns area. Some employees drive P passengers. When P==1 means driver transport work. You want ensure everyone able make work would like minimize number cars road. Requirements calculate number cars road : Every employee get town Every employee get town Every employee get town An employee travel car belonging employee towns Employees take rides employees live town The minimum number cars used Find whether possible everyone make work, is, many cars end driving office. Input One line containing integer C, number test cases input file. For test case be: One line containing integer N, number towns area integer T, town office located. One line containing integer E, number employees. E lines, one employee, containing: An integer H >= 1, home town employee, followed An integer P >= 0, number passengers drive. If employee licensed drive number 0. Output C lines, one test case order occur input file, followed by: The string IMPOSSIBLE, enough drivers everyone commute; OR N space-separated integers, one town 1 N, indicate number vehicles commuting town. Limits 1 ≤ T ≤ N 1 ≤ H ≤ N 0 ≤ P ≤ 6 Sample Input 3 5 1 3 1 0 1 0 1 0 5 1 3 2 4 2 0 3 0 5 3 5 1 2 1 0 4 2 4 4 4 0 Output 0 0 0 0 0 IMPOSSIBLE 1 0 0 1 0 Author: apurvsinghgaut Editorial: https://discuss.codechef.com/problems/MKWRK Tags: apurvsinghgaut, sorting Difficulty Rating: N/A Date Added: 21-09-2016 Time Limit: 1 secs Source Limit: 50000 Bytes Languages: PYTH 3.6, JAVA, C, CPP14, PYTH, PYP3, CS2, ADA, PYPY, TEXT, PAS fpc, NODEJS, RUBY, PHP, GO, HASK, TCL, PERL, SCALA, LUA, BASH, JS, LISP sbcl, PAS gpc, BF, CLOJ, D, CAML, FORT, ASM, FS, WSPC, LISP clisp, SCM guile, PERL6, ERL, CLPS, PRLG, ICK, NICE, ICON, SCM chicken, PIKE, SCM qobi, ST, NEM Submit
